# ── Google Analytics 4 (GA4 Data API) ──────────────────────
# Service Account credentials (server-side only, never exposed to browser)
#
# SETUP:
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console > Create Project (or use existing)
# 2. Enable "Google Analytics Data API" in APIs & Services > Library
# 3. Create Service Account: IAM & Admin > Service Accounts > Create
#    - Name: "ga4-dashboard" (any name)
#    - No extra roles needed at project level
# 4. Create key: Service Account > Keys > Add Key > JSON
#    - Download the JSON file
#    - Copy client_email and private_key values below
# 5. In GA4: Admin > Property > Property Access Management
#    - Add the service account email as "Viewer"
# 6. GA4 Property ID: Admin > Property Settings > Property ID (numeric)
#    - This is saved per-client in the dashboard Settings page (not here)
#
# TEST: After setup, go to /creatives/configuracoes, enter the Property ID,
#       then visit /creatives/paginas to see real GA4 data.
#
GA4_CLIENT_EMAIL=your-service-account@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com
GA4_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYOUR_KEY_HERE\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
